My NotesThe set of real numbers can be extended to complex numbers. This set of numbers arose, historically, from the question of whether a negative number can have a square root.

For example, what are the roots of \(x^{2}=-1\)?

From this problem, a new number was discovered: the square root of negative one. This number is denoted by i, i.e. i = \(\sqrt{-1}\), a symbol assigned by Leonhard Euler (1707-83, Swiss mathematician).

Complex numbers have applications in a variety of sciences and related areas such as signal processing, control theory, electromagnetism, quantum mechanics, cartography, and many others.

